I"Ô<p>In a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/continuous-state-dynamical-systems-share-a-common-structure">dynamical system</a>, bifurcations are critical values of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/argmin-and-argmax-formalize-optimization">control parameters</a>. Those values are located just between two different basins of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/attractors-and-repellors-have-opposite-behaviors-in-dynamical-systems">attraction</a> of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/structural-stability-describes-basin-of-similar-dynamical-systems">structurally stable</a> <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/dynamical-systems-have-a-certain-anatomy">dynamical systems</a>.</p>
